comments: Randle (NYK) establishes himself in Huerter's (SAC) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Lyles (SAC) jumps vertically and absorbs the ensuing contact that occurs during Barrett's (NYK) driving shot attempt.
Sabonis (SAC) cleanly blocks the shot attempt before it touches the backboard.
Sabonis (SAC) maintains his arms within the frame of his body and does not deliver illegal contact to Hart (NYK) during the pick.
Randle (NYK) legally contests Fox's (SAC) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Hartenstein (NYK) moves laterally into Fox's (SAC) path, but the contact is marginal and he is able to move through it.
Quickley (NYK) contests the shot and marginal contact occurs with Lyles' (SAC) arm after the release on his jump shot attempt.
Hartenstein (NYK) places both hands on Sabonis's (SAC) side/back during the rebound and he releases as the ball bounces overhead.
Barnes (SAC) rests his hand toward Randle's (NYK) waist and marginal contact occurs during his driving shot attempt.
Huerter (SAC) is firming up over his right leg when marginal contact occurs with Hart (NYK) during the pick.
Hartenstein (NYK) maintains verticality and absorbs the contact that occurs during Fox's (SAC) driving shot attempt.
Mitchell (SAC) delivers body contact to Randle (NYK) and affects Randle's SQBR during the drive.
Barnes (SAC) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Randle (NYK) prior to incidental arm contact occurring.
Randle (NYK) commits a foul on Lyles (SAC).
Lyles (SAC) brings his arm forward and absorbs the marginal contact as he moves alongside Barrett's (NYK) path during the driving shot attempt.
Quickley (NYK) commits a take foul on Fox (SAC).
Barnes (SAC) bring his hand toward Hart's (NYK) back as marginal contact occurs prior to releasing the pass at the end of his drive.
Barnes (SAC) moves alongside Barrett's (NYK) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Grimes (NYK) commits a take foul on Sabonis (SAC).
Sabonis (SAC) legally contests Randle's (NYK) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
